{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, developing improved segmentation models and datasets will pave the way for data assimilation into operando analysis and numerical simulations of in situ microstructures obtained experimentally and for application to process informatics.",
    "In functional materials, the controlling of the microstructures that dominate the material performance is essential.",
    "Recently, research on the multidimensionality of the obtained structural information has been developing.",
    "One example is the acquisition of three-dimensional (3D) spatial observations.",
    "Typical methods for obtaining 3D structures include optical microscopy and X-ray computed tomography [1] [2] [3] [4] [5] [6] [7], serial sectioning [8] [9] [10] [11] [12] using a scanning electron microscope with a focused ion beam (FIB-SEM), and transmission electron microscope computed tomography [13] [14] [15]."
  ]
}